				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The regulator converts the varying voltage coming out of the power brick to a more or less constant 5.0 V DC. Little to none of the mains frequency remains, and the PPU generates the 60.1 or 50 Hz time base from a crystal oscillator in the Control Deck. NTSC and PAL decks have different crystals and different PPUs.</div>

