						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">FinalZero wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">On an interesting note, in my sprite handling code, &quot;state&quot; is also used as the animation number. I grabbed that idea from Capcom.</div><br />What do you mean by &quot;animation number&quot;?</div><br />Oops. In my engine, an actor can have multiple animations. Each animation is just a list of sprites to use, and the speed at which the animation plays. So each actor is given a list of animations it can use, and by &quot;animation number&quot;, I just meant the index into this list. For example, for a player actor, I can have animation #0 be the player standing, animation #1 be a walking animation, animation #2 be a climbing animation, etc.</div>

