					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">NTSC and PAL are differing video formats, both in color encoding and frame rate. So they have two different NES consoles to handle this difference. It just happens that in many 50Hz mains countries, they use PAL, and in many 60Hz countries, they use NTSC (because originally the video standards were influenced by the mains frequency).</div>

