					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">What changed was better electrical engineering techniques that allowed better isolation of signals, but the signal standards that TVs expected were already fixed a decade before the Atari 2600.<br /><br />Games have already moved on to digital HDMI signals, but the major consoles' advantage over a PC is still that they come with the ability to fall back to a signal that works on legacy (pre-2007) SDTVs without an obscure scan converter cable sold only online. And for this, yes, most games are expected to run at the refresh rate of the region's respective analog video standard.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

